Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are pleased to bring to market for sale 20 Joseph Street Blackburn North via expressions of interest closing Wednesday 23rd October 2019 at 3pm AEST. The sale presents an opportunity for owner occupiers or investors to secure an office warehouse in the tightly held and niche industrial precinct of Blackburn North. Joseph Street abuts the M3 Eastern Freeway and is in direct proximity of Box Hill and Doncaster which is accessed via Middleborough Road. Surrounding national occupiers positioned in Joseph Street include AP Eagers, Ambulance Victoria and Arlec Australia.

Location Details
• M3 Eastern Freeway 241m*
• Middleborough Road 264m*
• Doncaster Westfield 2.1km*
• Box Hill CBD 2.75km*
• Golden Mile retail precinct 2km*
• Laburnum Railway Station 2.3km*

Property Details
• Industrial 3 Zone
• Total building area 1,334sqm*
• Total land area 1,514sqm*
• 2 roller shutter doors providing drive through access
• Offered vacant possession / short term lease back
• Temperature controlled lab space to be kept or removed by vendor subject to purchaser preference

For further information please contact exclusive selling agents Joe Brzezek and Sasan Misaghian from CBRE. The expression of interest deadline is Wednesday 23rd of October 2019 AEST.

*approx.

CBRE is excited to present 31-35 Cottage Street, Blackburn to the market for sale via Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday 8th September at 3pm (AEST). 

Situated only metres from Maroondah Highway, this free standing industrial facility offers unbeatable access to the Eastern Freeway, Springvale Road and Whitehorse Road. 

Located in the tightly held industrial pocket of Blackburn the property benefits from the abundance of surrounding amenity on the Golden Mile which is home to over 265 businesses, this opportunity is one not to be missed. Surrounding occupiers include, Lexus, Nissan, Fantastic Furniture, Officeworks, Freedom Furniture and Bunnings Warehouse.

Property details include:

+ 929sqm* Total building area
+ 25sqm* Office space
+ 904sqm* Warehouse/amenity  
+ 1,666sqm* land area
+ 2 Roller doors 
+ High power supply
+ Gas available
+ 20 Car parking locations 
+ Industrial 1 zone


Location highlights include:
+ Whitehorse Road 250m*
+ Blackburn Railway Station 700m*
+ Springvale Road 1.6km*
+ M3 Eastern Freeway 2.5km*
+ Box Hill Central 3km*
+ Melbourne CBD 16km*

 
To request a contracts or arrange a site inspection, please contact one of CBRE’s exclusively appointed selling agents.

CBRE is pleased to bring to market for the first time in 60 years, 18 and 20 Cottage Street Blackburn. The site is situated within the tightly held industrial suburb of Blackburn which is 17km* east of the Melbourne CBD. The property has excellent access to surrounding arterials being only 200m* from Whitehorse Rd and  2.5km* from M3 Eastern Freeway.

Cottage Street is surrounded by an abundance of amenity being within meters of the Golden mile which is home to over 265 businesses including shopping centres such as Home HQ and Brand Smart. Major occupiers include, Lexus, Nissan, Natuzzi, Fantastic Furniture, Officeworks, Freedom Furniture and Bunnings Warehouse. Blackburn station is within 500m* walking distance of the property, however buses also provide direct linkages via Whitehorse Road.
